TI  - International Business Education: A Corporate View
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 553
EP  - 564
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
AB  - As a preliminary step in the internationalization of business school curricula, 122 major Canadian corporations were surveyed for their views on the importance of various management skills and international courses, as well as their opinion on the mechanisms (Institutions and academics) for delivering them. This article reports on the responses obtained and suggests methods for improving the overall effectiveness of international business education.
