TY  - JOUR
AU  - Martinez, Jon I.
AU  - Jarillo, J. Carlos
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/09/01
TI  - The Evolution of Research on Coordination Mechanisms in Multinational Corporations
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 489
EP  - 514
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
AB  - The mechanisms of coordination used by Multinational Corporations (MNCs) are studied, through an exhaustive literature review. A pattern of evolution is found: as time has passed, researchers have concentrated more on subtler and informal mechanisms, abandoning their unidimensional focus on structural issues. It is suggested that the increase in the study of those mechanisms may be due, among other reasons, to the fact that MNCs are indeed making more use of them. That could be explained by changes in the international competitive environment, which force firms to adjust their strategies, requiring ever more multidimensional coordination.
SN  - 1478-6990
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1057/palgrave.jibs.8490370
DO  - 10.1057/palgrave.jibs.8490370
ID  - Martinez1989
