TY  - JOUR
AU  - Adler, Nancy J.
AU  - Graham, John L.
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/09/01
TI  - Cross-Cultural Interaction: The International Comparison Fallacy?
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 515
EP  - 537
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
AB  - International management studies have been based primarily on the comparison of managerial behavior in countries around the world. Often, these studies have implied that business-people behave similarly with their domestic colleagues as with their foreign counterparts. In questioning that assumption, this study tests whether intra-cultural behavior accurately predicts cross-cultural behavior. Using a negotiation simulation and a sample of 462 Japanese, American, and Canadian businesspeople, behaviors in cross-cultural negotiations were found to differ in some important ways from those in intra-cultural negotiations.
